Dear Hiring Team,

It is with great pleasure that I submit my candidacy for the *Sr Software Engineer, Hub Cloud Services* role with *SmartThings*. I bring over three years of professional software engineering experience across cloud backends and AI-driven systems, along with a strong academic foundation as a Master of Science in Computer Science graduate from Pace University, NY.

Through my experience across two engineering roles, I have built and delivered production-grade backend systems that directly reflect the technical requirements of this position, including *scalable microservices*, *REST APIs*, *multi-threading and concurrency*, and cloud reliability. At Sperse, I built a service layer that translated natural-language intents into safe, validated tool calls across *1000+ platform endpoints*, and I architected *highly available* and *fault-tolerant* event/command pipelines with LangChain and LangGraph. I also owned cloud services deployments, monitoring, and production support using Langfuse and LangSmith. At Qualitest, I developed cloud services across AWS and Google Cloud, built Java/Spring Boot integrations for identity workflows serving *30+ applications*, and implemented Step Functions pipelines to protect long-running jobs from Lambda timeouts. This background prepares me to contribute meaningfully to the Hub Cloud Services team's core responsibilities in API reliability, automation throughput, and platform quality.

My research experience at the Pace Artificial Intelligence Lab reinforced the engineering discipline and collaborative culture your team values. I built repeatable model training and inference workflows with CUDA, PyTorch, vLLM, and Hugging Face, and served as a mentor to *+50* students through hands-on workshops in GPU systems and agent orchestration. That blend of rigorous execution and knowledge sharing aligns well with the role's emphasis on leadership, ownership, and strong cross-team communication.

I am especially motivated by SmartThings' mission to create the most effortless way for anyone to build a smart home and by its focus on secure, reliable, seamless connected-home experiences. I would value the opportunity to contribute to that goal by helping the Hub Cloud Services team deliver cloud and hub automation that feels instant, dependable, and simple for users. I would love to discuss my interest in this position with your team and can be reached at #ph or #eml. Thank you for your time and consideration, I look forward to connecting!

